org.hkijena.jipipe.api.nodes

Class JIPipeGraphNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.nodes.JIPipeGraphNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JIPipeValidatable, JIPipeParameterCollection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JIPipeAlgorithm, JIPipeCommentNode, JIPipeProjectCompartment

    public abstract class JIPipeGraphNode
extends Object
implements JIPipeValidatable, JIPipeParameterCollection
    A node is a set of input and output data slots, and a run() function It is part of the JIPipeGraph. The workload of this node is considered optional (this means it can have an empty workload), which is important for structural graphs like the compartment graph. Use JIPipeAlgorithm as base class to indicate a non-optional workload.
